review_blob: Delicious. So much better than last years version. Smoky and malty. Good yeast character. Not crazy boozy like old version. Great finish

A- dark brown. Murky.
A- smells like the beach. Sweet & tropical
T- sweet coconut. Coffee. Nuttiness and malt heavy
M- slick and luscious, coats the palate just long enough before washing away
O- not my usual cup of tea, but I enjoyed this. Well done

Really liking this. Mouthfeel is a little too sticky for my kind of ipa, but thats being critical.
Lots of orange grapefruit and tropical aromas, taste follows.
Great stuff
Love this, so rich. Tastes like a liquified dark chocolate bar. Too bad its 10%, cant drink too many
A very boring beer. Its got potential, and it is probably a good introductory craft beer for newcomers
A passable pale ale and a decent local offering, but not memorable overall.
Easily my favorite. Better than barrel aged for me. Like this base. Everything an oatmeal stout should be
Not my style. Just not enough here to wow me really. A good Oktoberfest. Fine. Moving on
Dang. This is more like an English ipa at first, so malty. But then those big hops come on strong. Well balanced in the end
Absolutely awesome. This beer has loads of nutty aromas and the taste follows on. Smooth and creamy mouthfeel too.
Great take on classic style. Nice blend of bitterness and malts. Could drink on this all day. What?!? Its available in cans?? Yes please!
Love this! Great hop aroma, gorgeous color. Mouthfeel is spot on and the bitterness is just enough to be ipa without getting in way of session ability
Its a Pilsner. It has some flavor, but not enough for me. Also, couldve had soon in flight...
Love this. Easy drinking, but with flavor. Not a huge fan of reds, but this has enough character to work
A good wheat. A little happier than desired, but good. Very present mouth feel. Good drinking
Smells very hot. A little cloudy looking and thin on the mouth. Strong alcohol heat blends well with smooth flavor
beer_name: Core Bourbon Barrel Aged Oatmeal Stout
